<div class="page">
  <main>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-title">
        <h1>Knyle Share foundation</h1>
      </div>

      <div class="home-grid">
        <section class="home-card">
          <h2>Admin host</h2>
          <p>The Rails admin area is wired to the configured admin host and is currently rendering prototype-backed placeholder screens.</p>
          <div class="home-actions">
            <a class="btn btn-primary" href="http://<%= admin_host %>:3000">Open admin on <%= admin_host %></a>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="home-card">
          <h2>Public host</h2>
          <p>The public bundle host is reserved for bundle delivery. It is not implemented yet, but the route boundary is now explicit.</p>
          <div class="home-actions">
            <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="http://<%= public_host %>:3000">Open public host on <%= public_host %></a>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</div>
